snippet.textDisplay: The judges decision was based on procedural fairness.  Novak asked border security to give him until 8:30 a.m. to get in touch with his lawyers, Australian tennis.  At around 7:40 a.m. he was told that his Visa was cancelled and that he had to leave or appeal.  He chose to appeal and was put up in a hotel housing people attempting to enter Australia under "refugee" status.  Had border security just given him the extra hour - (he wasn't asking for days and days -  this debacle could have been avoided.  And in a nutshell the denial to allow ND to consult with his lawyers is why the judge (Anthony Kelley) found that border security acted "unreasonably".   This case had to do with procedural fairness - and it applies to all people.  p.s. The other players who left due to Visa issues did so because they chose not to appeal.  That was their own choice - and has nothing to do with being number 1 or number 100.
